         <div type="translation" resp="#jmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> of <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> unconquered Augustus, chief priest, victor in Germany, greatest <supplied reason="lost">Uictor</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> holding tribunician power <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>  </p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Maximinus is the earliest emperor whose titles would conform; but Gallienus,
            Claudius Gothicus, Aurelian, Probus, Carus, Carinus and Diocletian are all
            possible. The style of the monument appears to have been of the third century.</p>
         </div>
